---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---
<DocsLayout title="Agent Status Monitoring — Band Docs">
  <h1>Agent Status Monitoring</h1>
  <p>
    Band continuously monitors the status of coding agents running in your workspaces. Agent
    status is displayed as a colored indicator dot on each workspace card, giving you an
    at-a-glance view of what every agent is doing across all your projects.
  </p>

  <h2>Status Types</h2>
  <p>
    Each workspace's coding agent can be in one of these states:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Waiting (no indicator)</strong> &mdash; The agent is idle. No task is running and no
      agent activity has been detected. No indicator dot is shown in this state.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Working (animated dot)</strong> &mdash; The agent is actively executing a task.
      The indicator uses the <code>bg-status-working</code> color and pulses while the agent
      is making progress &mdash; reading files, writing code, or running commands.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Needs attention (static dot)</strong> &mdash; The agent has finished its current
      task or requires human input (for example, it called <code>AskUserQuestion</code> or
      <code>ExitPlanMode</code>). The indicator uses the
      <code>bg-status-needs-attention</code> color. Review the agent's output and either
      provide input, approve changes, or start a new task.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <figure class="my-6 mx-auto max-w-sm overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border shadow-lg">
    <img
      src="/screenshot-agent-working.png"
      alt="A workspace row labelled main with a pulsing dot indicator showing the agent is currently working."
      width="252"
      height="44"
      loading="lazy"
      decoding="async"
      class="block h-auto w-full"
    />
    <figcaption class="border-t border-border bg-card/50 px-4 py-2 text-center text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      Working &mdash; the agent is actively making progress on a task.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure class="my-6 mx-auto max-w-sm overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border shadow-lg">
    <img
      src="/screenshot-agent-needs-attention.png"
      alt="A workspace row labelled main with a static dot indicator showing the agent needs attention."
      width="256"
      height="40"
      loading="lazy"
      decoding="async"
      class="block h-auto w-full"
    />
    <figcaption class="border-t border-border bg-card/50 px-4 py-2 text-center text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      Needs attention &mdash; the agent has stopped or is asking for input.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2>How Status Is Detected</h2>
  <p>
    Band detects agent status through <strong>Claude Code hooks</strong>. When the Band dashboard
    installs hooks (prompted on first launch), it registers hook handlers that fire on key
    Claude Code lifecycle events.
  </p>
  <p>
    The hooks use the <code>band notify</code> command to send status updates to the Band server:
  </p>
  <pre><code set:html={`echo '{"hook_event_name":"Stop","cwd":"/path/to/worktree"}' | band notify`}></code></pre>
  <p>
    The Band server processes these notifications and updates the agent status for the
    corresponding workspace. Status changes are broadcast to the dashboard in real-time
    via server-sent events (SSE).
  </p>

  <h3>Hook Events</h3>
  <p>
    Five Claude Code hook events are wired up on first launch (see
    <code>apps/web/src/lib/hooks.ts</code>):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>UserPromptSubmit</strong> &mdash; A new prompt has been sent. Transitions to <em>working</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>PreToolUse</strong> &mdash; A tool call is about to run. Stays <em>working</em> in general; switches to <em>needs attention</em> when the tool is <code>AskUserQuestion</code> or <code>ExitPlanMode</code>, since both require a human reply.</li>
    <li><strong>PermissionRequest</strong> &mdash; The agent needs permission to proceed (e.g. an unapproved tool). Stays <em>working</em>; the dashboard surfaces the request inline.</li>
    <li><strong>PostToolUse</strong> &mdash; A tool call has finished. Stays <em>working</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>Stop</strong> &mdash; The agent has stopped (task completed or exited). Transitions to <em>needs attention</em>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Status Display</h2>
  <p>
    Agent status is displayed in two locations:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Workspace list</strong> &mdash; A small colored dot appears next to the branch name in the project list. This is always visible and provides a quick summary.</li>
    <li><strong>Workspace detail view</strong> &mdash; When viewing a workspace in the web interface, the status is shown alongside other workspace metadata.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notification Sounds</h2>
  <p>
    Band can play a notification sound when an agent transitions from <em>working</em> to
    <em>needs attention</em>. This is useful when you have multiple agents running and want
    to know when one finishes without constantly watching the dashboard.
  </p>
  <p>
    To enable notification sounds, go to <a href="/docs/settings">Settings</a> and toggle
    <strong>Notification sound</strong> on. You can choose from several built-in sounds and
    preview them before saving.
  </p>

  <h2>Installing Hooks</h2>
  <p>
    If Claude Code hooks are not installed, the dashboard shows a setup prompt at the bottom:
  </p>
  <pre><code>Install Claude Code hooks for agent status detection  [Install]</code></pre>
  <p>
    Click <strong>Install</strong> to set up the hooks. This configures Claude Code to send
    lifecycle notifications to Band automatically. The hooks are installed globally and apply
    to all Claude Code sessions on your machine.
  </p>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>No status showing</strong> &mdash; Make sure Claude Code hooks are installed
      (check the dashboard for the install prompt). Verify the Band server is running.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Status stuck on "working"</strong> &mdash; This can happen if the agent process
      was terminated without sending a stop notification. Restarting the agent or creating a
      new task will reset the status.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Hooks prompt keeps appearing</strong> &mdash; Another tool may be overwriting
      the Claude Code hooks configuration. Check your Claude Code settings for conflicting
      hook definitions.
    </li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
